rejected.py is a multi-threaded AMQP 0-8 consumer framework. It has been developed for and tested against RabbitMQ 1.6.0. For more information, check out the wiki on the main GitHub page: http://github.com/gmr/rejected.py

Features Include:

 * Elastic scaling of consumers based upon demand
 * Specify a min # of consumers, max # of consumers and threshold to spawn new threads
 * Throttling of messages per second
 * Allows for multiple brokers per binding

Requirements:

 * amqplib
 * pyyaml
 * alice (optional)